Below is the **complete financial governance and system architecture** for:

# üî∑ LOGIC 12 ‚Äì Procurement Budgeting & Spend Control Logic

This logic ensures that **no procurement action occurs outside approved financial limits**, and that commitments are continuously aligned with organizational financial plans, cash flow strategy, and fiscal controls.

It transforms procurement from a transactional activity into a **financially disciplined control system**.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ PURPOSE OF LOGIC 12

This logic ensures:

* Every procurement is linked to an approved budget
* Real-time tracking of committed vs available funds
* Automatic prevention of overspending
* Multi-period forecasting (monthly / annual / project-based)
* Visibility of total organizational spend

It prevents:

* Budget overruns
* Hidden commitments
* Unplanned liabilities
* Cash flow misalignment
* End-of-year spending shocks

---

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ WHERE THIS LOGIC OPERATES

Budget control is embedded at:

| Stage                        | Budget Interaction             |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Procurement request creation | Budget availability check      |
| Tender publication           | Pre-commitment reservation     |
| Award decision               | Commitment confirmation        |
| Contract amendment           | Budget revalidation            |
| Payment milestone            | Liquidation of committed funds |

This logic integrates tightly with Logic 11 (Approval) and Logic 10 (Award).

---

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ CORE FINANCIAL CONCEPTS

---

## üîπ A. Budget Allocation

Predefined financial limits assigned to:

* Departments
* Projects
* Cost centers
* Programs
* Categories
* Funding sources (internal, donor, grant)

---

## üîπ B. Budget Types Supported

* Annual operating budget
* Capital expenditure (CAPEX) budget
* Project-based budget
* Multi-year budget
* Grant-based restricted funding
* Rolling forecast budgets

---

## üîπ C. Budget Status Variables

For each budget line:

```
Total Approved Budget
‚Äì Committed Amount
‚Äì In-Process Reserved Amount
‚Äì Actual Spend
= Available Budget
```

---

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ FINANCIAL CONTROL FLOW

```
Procurement Need Created (Logic 3)
        ‚Üì
Budget Line Selection Required
        ‚Üì
System Checks Available Funds
        ‚Üì
If Available ‚Üí Reserve Funds
If Not Available ‚Üí Block or Escalate
        ‚Üì
Tender Published
        ‚Üì
Award Finalized ‚Üí Commitment Confirmed
        ‚Üì
Contract Execution
        ‚Üì
Payments Deduct from Commitment
        ‚Üì
Remaining Balance Updated
```

---

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ BUDGET VALIDATION ENGINE

---

## üîπ A. Pre-Commitment Check

Before tender publication:

```
Estimated Procurement Value ‚â§ Available Budget?
```

If NO:

* Block action
* Trigger budget adjustment workflow
* Escalate to Finance approval

---

## üîπ B. Commitment Reservation

When tender is approved:

* Estimated value is temporarily reserved
* Budget is marked as ‚ÄúCommitted (Pending Award)‚Äù

Prevents double allocation.

---

## üîπ C. Award Commitment Lock

Upon award:

* Final contract value replaces estimated value
* Commitment becomes binding
* Difference adjusted automatically

---

# 6Ô∏è‚É£ REAL-TIME SPEND TRACKING

System updates in real time:

* Contract awards
* Amendments
* Payment releases
* Cancellation refunds

Dashboard shows:

* Budget consumption rate
* Departmental burn rate
* Project financial health
* Category-level spend

---

# 7Ô∏è‚É£ AMENDMENT IMPACT CONTROL

If contract amendment increases value:

System recalculates:

```
New Total Commitment =
Original Contract
+ All Amendments
```

If new total exceeds available budget:

* Block amendment
* Require budget reallocation
* Escalate approval (Logic 11)

Prevents incremental overspending.

---

# 8Ô∏è‚É£ MULTI-PERIOD FORECASTING

Supports:

* Monthly forecasting
* Quarterly projections
* Annual rollover planning
* Multi-year commitments

Forecast model:

```
Committed Value
+ Expected Procurement Pipeline
+ Planned Renewals
= Projected Future Spend
```

Helps finance anticipate cash flow impact.

---

# 9Ô∏è‚É£ CASH FLOW ALIGNMENT

Budget logic can also track:

* Payment schedule per contract
* Milestone-based disbursements
* Advance payments
* Retention release dates

Allows:

* Monthly liquidity forecasting
* Payment clustering risk identification

---

# üîü CROSS-FUNDING SOURCE CONTROL

If procurement uses:

* Donor funds
* Grant funds
* Restricted project funds

System enforces:

* Spending within funding agreement scope
* Category restrictions
* Reporting segregation

Prevents fund misuse.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ BUDGET REALLOCATION WORKFLOW

If additional funds required:

```
Request Budget Adjustment
        ‚Üì
Finance Review
        ‚Üì
Approval or Rejection
        ‚Üì
Budget Updated
```

All changes logged.

No manual override without audit record.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ SPEND ANALYTICS LAYER

System generates:

* Spend by category
* Spend by supplier
* Spend by region
* Maverick spend detection
* Budget variance analysis
* Forecast accuracy ratio

Supports strategic sourcing decisions.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ OVERSPENDING PROTECTION RULES

System blocks:

* Tender publication without budget
* Award exceeding reserved amount
* Amendment exceeding threshold
* Payment beyond committed value

Optional tolerance (e.g., 5%) configurable.

---

